  17. module Int_base = Identifiable.Make (struct
  18.   type t = int

  20.   let compare x y = x - y
  21.   let output oc x = Printf.fprintf oc "%i" x
  22.   let hash i = i
  23.   let equal (i : int) j = i = j
  24.   let print = Format.pp_print_int
  25. end)

  27. module Int = struct
  28.   type t = int

  30.   include Int_base

  32.   let rec zero_to_n n =
  33.     if n < 0 then Set.empty else Set.add n (zero_to_n (n-1))

  35.   let to_string n = Int.to_string n
  36. end

  38. module Int8 = struct
  39.   type t = int

  41.   let zero = 0
  42.   let one = 1

  44.   let of_int_exn i =
  45.     if i < -(1 lsl 7) || i > ((1 lsl 7) - 1) then
  46.       Misc.fatal_errorf "Int8.of_int_exn: %d is out of range" i
  47.     else
  48.       i

  50.   let to_int i = i
  51. end

  53. module Int16 = struct
  54.   type t = int

  56.   let of_int_exn i =
  57.     if i < -(1 lsl 15) || i > ((1 lsl 15) - 1) then
  58.       Misc.fatal_errorf "Int16.of_int_exn: %d is out of range" i
  59.     else
  60.       i

  62.   let lower_int64 = Int64.neg (Int64.shift_left Int64.one 15)
  63.   let upper_int64 = Int64.sub (Int64.shift_left Int64.one 15) Int64.one

  65.   let of_int64_exn i =
  66.     if Int64.compare i lower_int64 < 0
  67.         || Int64.compare i upper_int64 > 0
  68.     then
  69.       Misc.fatal_errorf "Int16.of_int64_exn: %Ld is out of range" i
  70.     else
  71.       Int64.to_int i

  73.   let to_int t = t
  74. end

  76. module Float = struct
  77.   type t = float

  79.   include Identifiable.Make (struct
  80.     type t = float

  82.     let compare x y = Stdlib.compare x y
  83.     let output oc x = Printf.fprintf oc "%f" x
  84.     let hash f = Hashtbl.hash f
  85.     let equal (i : float) j = i = j
  86.     let print = Format.pp_print_float
  87.   end)
  88. end
